r your needs. You also have access to inspirational interviews.\r\n\r\nCountry Attire ? Best Place to Buy Mens Clothes Online\r\nSpecifically designed for the British attire, Country Attire is what you would be impressed with and find in tune with the stores like Urban Outfitters. The store offers you carefully chosen products to make you look fantastic and lively.\r\n\r\nThe site also has an option for the top end men?s shoes for an enhanced fashion statement. Offering a free global delivery, the site promises a matchless quality of fabric to your fashion needs. It sources the material both from the UK and around the world.\r\n\r\nRecommended Reading: Stores like Forever 21\r\n\r\nThread ? Best Mens Fashion Websites\r\nThread is not just an online store, but an excellent service that offers you a complete insight into what the fashion industry at large has to offer you. What makes the site unique in its approach is it will help you choose the fabric in tune with your taste.\r\n\r\nIf you are someone who does not have enough time to go through multiple stores and websites, this is the perfect option for you. The site comes with style advice at its best for all your fashion designing requirements you may have. One of the best men?s fashion store, Thread lives up to the expectations if you are looking for the ultimate in the stores like Urban Outfitters.\r\n\r\nIn Conclusion ? Stores like Urban Outfitters\r\nThose were a few online stores you can find offering you the same degree of performance when it comes to men?s fashion designing. Not that the list is exclusive in any manner, but it provides you a way to access clothing in the best possible way sitting in the comforts of your home.\r\n\r\nOf course, Urban Outfitters is a statement on its own and has established itself as one of the prominent options for an enhanced experience in terms of men?s clothing and fashion. If you are looking for similar stores like Urban Outfitters for a variety in your experience, the stores featured in the above compilation should ideally meet most of your requirements.\r\n\r\nHave you visited any of the stores outlined in this compilation? If you have, do share your thoughts, experiences, and opinions with us through the comments section here below. Also, share information about the other alternative options for the stores like Urban Outfitters.', 1, '2019-10-02 08:31:18', 3, 'img/Stores-like-Urban-Outfitters.jpg', 31, 1),
('10 Best Stores Like Charlotte Russe for Fashion Shopping', '\r\nFashion is in the trend, and when it comes to women, they went too far in the fashion than men. In this blog post we are going to talk about the stores like Charlotte Russe but let?s first know about this store.\r\n\r\nCharlotte Russe is an American online fashion store primarily for women. It was founded in 1975 by Daniel Lawrence and his two brothers. On this store, you can find women clothes, shoes, dresses, and other fashion accessories. Though Charlotte Russe is a great e-commerce store online, as human beings, we always look for some alternatives. Therefore, in this blog post, I am going to share 10 best stores like Charlotte Russe which you will find useful for your next shopping spree.\r\n\r\n10 Best Stores Like Charlotte Russe\r\nShein\r\nShein is a multinational online store and good for Indians as they have their Indian version as well. It is one of the best Charlotte Russe alternatives as it is one stop shop for all fashion needs of women.  From clothes to shoes and fashion accessories, you get everything in this store to shop.\r\n\r\nWebsite: Shein.in\r\n\r\nMissguided\r\nMissguided is another online store like Charlotte Russe that is primarily opened for Women?s fashion accessories and clothing. Their bold and sexy looking dresses tempt every woman to have a look at its product gallery. This is a modern-day online store. The website offers good discount to students to make things affordable for them. No matter what size you are or what type of dress you want, you get everything on Missguided at much affordable cost.\r\n\r\nWebsite: https://www.missguidedus.com\r\n\r\nLulus\r\nLulus is another a good store like Charlotte Russe but cheaper a bit. They have the latest trendy clothes from party wear to night dresses, lingerie, and even some sexy looking tops that you can buy at good cost. Customers are attracted to this store because of its awesome return policy.\r\n\r\nWebsite: https://www.lulus.com\r\n\r\nForever 21\r\nForever 21 is one of the best stores like Charlotte Russe, and it operates in multiple countries for targeting global customers. They have all the trendy clothing both for men and women. It is one of the most popular stores online for fashionable clothes.\r\n\r\nWebsite: http://www.forever21.com\r\n\r\nAlso Read: Stores like Forever 21\r\n\r\nPretty Little Thing\r\nThis is Australia based online store and a store like Charlotte Russe. All types of outfit women can get from this store at good prices. Matching shoes and other accessories are also there for sale that you can get along with clothes. This is a good store especially for women and one stop shop for all fashion needs.\r\n\r\nWebsite: https://www.prettylittlething.com.au\r\n\r\nBeginning Boutique\r\nBeginning Boutique is another good store like Charlotte Russe. This online store is the best shop to buy clothes, jewelry, shoes, etc. This is just another one stop shop for all your fashion needs. They have the latest trendy dresses that you can buy for you for any occasion be it your wedding or first wedding night or summer vacation or night wear; everything you can get from here at good prices.\r\n\r\nWebsite: https://www.beginningboutique.com.au\r\n\r\nReformation\r\nReformation is one of the best online stores like Charlotte Russe. In fact, better in many manners. The store focuses on its own design rather than others?. They are US based store, but they ship to abroad as well, but US shipping is free as it is written on their homepage. Since they sell their own manufactured products, they do take care of their customer well in order to keep things going well for them. You can get trendiest clothes on this website.\r\n\r\nWebsite: https://www.thereformation.com/\r\n\r\nDorothy Perkins\r\nThis is said to be the UK version of Charlotte Russe. This online store sells products only for women and kids currently. Everything you can get on this site whether you want to shop for clothes, shoes, boots, lingerie, bags, and other accessories. Additionally, you can shop for your kids on this store as well. It offers almost all sizes that make things easier for every type of buyers whether she is tall, curvy, short or slim.\r\n\r\nWebsite: http://www.dorothyperkins.com\r\n\r\nUniqlo\r\nThis fashion store offers celebrity-inspired clothes and accessories. They have different categories for Men, Women, Kids, Boys, and Girls that make the search easier when you land on its website to browse and shop.\r\n\r\nWebsite: https://www.uniqlo.com\r\n\r\nLove Culture\r\nBeing a woman, you will fall in love with this online fashion store because it offers everything that you might like to shop to fulfill your fashion needs. You will get all types of dresses, clothes, fashion accessories, shoes, etc. at affordable prices. If you are one who loves to wear some sexy stuff, this online store is for you because you will get awesome dresses out here to flaunt your beauty.\r\n\r\nWebsite: http://www.loveculture.com\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\nNowadays everyone is fashion freak. There is kind of competition of looking the best, and that is the reason we go far in the fashion. Especially women are very selective about everything wear be it clothes, sandals, earrings, necklace, etc. That is why they need online fashion stores rather than a general online store with a low number of trendy stuff. Fashion stores have more in their database, and that is why here we have listed 10 best stores like Charlotte Russe which is itself a great fashion store.', 1, '2019-10-02 08:32:42', 3, 'img/10-Best-Stores-Like-Charlotte-Russe.jpg', 32, 1),
('Intro to SEO for your E-commerce website', '\r\nWhile every website, regardless of its function or niche, should always adhere to standard SEO best practices across the board, taking your SEO to the next level is a little different for e-commerce sites. This is because your visitors? intent is different ? they?re (hopefully!) looking to buy a product, rather than just searching for general information on a topic.\r\n\r\nThey?ve probably already got something in mind, but want to explore their options, compare different products and prices, and ideally receive some tailored suggestions from you. We take a look at the basics of SEO specifically for e-commerce websites and online stores.\r\n\r\nChoose your platform wisely\r\nUnlike a standard company website with just a few pages dedicated to different services, e-commerce sites can end up with thousands of pages dedicated to different product lines, variations, groupings, colors, styles, and themes.\r\n\r\nAs with any website, the more pages, and unique URLs you have, the harder it gets to keep everything optimized the way it should be. If you get off to a bad start and are making even minor errors from the beginning, they can become a nightmare to fix (or even find) months down the line.\r\n\r\nUnless you?re extremely confident in your web development abilities, building your site on a dedicated e-commerce platform makes a lot more sense. Many offer free trials so you can get a feel for whether you like the interface or not. In addition, several platforms ?like Shopify and WooComerce for example? already have a host of built-in SEO features to make your life easier. These usually include things like ?automagic? 301 redirects and canonical tags for duplicate content, social sharing buttons and automatic generation of your website?s sitemap.xml and robots.txt files.\r\n\r\nIf you do decide to go it on your own, however, then make absolutely sure you?re using HTTPS across your entire website, so your customers? personal details are encrypted. If you?re using a platform like WordPress, make sure to get familiar with the Yoast SEO plugin, which will offer tips along the way, and help you get your content SEO-ready before you publish.\r\n\r\nGet to grips with keyword research\r\nWith standard websites, keyword research usually involves looking for topics that get high search volumes but don?t have so much competition that there?s little chance of ranking for them. For e-commerce websites, you?re trying to be a bit more specific ? attracting highly targeted traffic that?s ready to convert. That said, you?re still following the same basic formula.\r\n\r\nAnother great way to get keyword and topic ideas is to get inspiration from your competitors! Giants like Amazon and any top-ranking e-commerce sites in your niche are the perfect place to begin. See what keywords they?re ranking for (a clue you should aim for different, more specific long-tail keywords), what their site architecture is like, and any obvious weak spots, like categories which have thin content you know you could easily flesh out.\r\n\r\nSearching your major keywords on Google and checking the ?People also ask? and ?Searches related to? boxes can also be a quick and simple option to get some general ideas. Once you have your basic keywords and phrases, you can then use whichever keyword research tool you prefer to expand on your ideas, compare search volumes, find LSI keywords, and start building up a list of potential topics to create content, pages and blog posts around.\r\n\r\nKeyword research is going to be a critical factor in your success, so if you?re not confident in your ability to do it thoroughly enough, then rather partner with an established SEO company like Ruby Digital who can. Remember also that you?ll need to revisit your keyword strategy from time to time. Changing consumer demand, new competitors arriving on the scene, and new products entering the market can all have an effect on which keywords will perform best. If you can spot a trend before the competition and get your content out there first, you can attract a valuable source of new, ready-to-buy traffic.\r\n\r\nGet the technical basics right\r\nIf you already have an existing e-commerce site, then identifying site errors with a free tool like Screaming Frog is a must. Tools like this crawl your website, links, and images for SEO errors like duplicate pages, meta titles and descriptions, missing header tags, redirects, and much more. You?ll want to sort these out before you start adding any new content and check back from time to time to ensure you?re not falling back into bad habits.\r\n\r\nIf you?re using an e-commerce platform with built-in SEO tools already, then remember you should still be including any relevant keywords in the following:\r\n\r\nImage file names\r\nImage alt text\r\nThe URLs of all product pages, blog posts, and category/topic pages\r\nUse internal linking to create a customer journey\r\nWhen someone visits an e-commerce site, they?re probably looking to compare similar products. Whenever you add a new product, consider what someone with a higher or lower budget might be interested in, and make sure you entice them to check out these options using internal links and thumbnail images.\r\n\r\nMake your content entertaining, informative and easy to read\r\nKeeping sentences and paragraphs short, breaking up long stretches of text with images or videos, and organizing product data in a logical, easy-to-follow manner can all help keep visitors on your site for longer.\r\n\r\nThis not just good for your rankings but gives you more time to convince them to hit that ?Add to cart? button!\r\n\r\nOptimize your page load speeds\r\nWe live in the kind of world where people start to get antsy if a website takes longer than three seconds to load. Conversely, making sure your site loads that much faster than a big competitor?s can be a pretty effective way to encourage visitors to purchase from you instead.\r\n\r\nYou can use a free tool like Pingdom or Google?s PageSpeed Insights tool to see where you stand and then act accordingly to improve it by optimizing images, leveraging browser caching, ?minifying? CSS and removing redirects.\r\n\r\nWhile doing it right takes time, an e-commerce site which focuses on the right keywords, loads quickly across different devices, and always adheres to best SEO practices can be massively rewarding!', 2, '2019-10-02 08:38:47', 4, 'img/ecom-1.png', 33, 1);
